Standard Bank Boosted CEO Maree’s Pay by 9.7% in 2010

-- B y   R e n e e   B o n o r c h i s
-- 
2011-05-04T08:36:25Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-28/standard-bank-ceo-s-compensation-doubled-last-year-even-as-profit-declined.html
(Corrects to show that CEO must pay 111.94 rand for shares
in second paragraph of story first published on April 28.)  Standard Bank  Group Ltd.,  Africa ’s
largest bank, increased the pay of Chief Executive Officer Jacko Maree by 9.7 percent in 2010, even as profit declined.  Maree, 56, was paid 6.53 million rand ($983,000) last year,
including base pay, pension contributions and other benefits,
and will not receive a performance bonus for the second year,
according to the Johannesburg-based bank’s  annual report . Maree
was allocated the option to buy 500,000 shares in March last
year. He can buy the shares, awarded to him for the lender’s
2009 performance, at 111.94 rand apiece when they vest over the
next three to five years on condition earnings improve, it said.  The bank said on Oct. 21 last year it would cut as many as
2,100 jobs in  London  and Johannesburg to reduce expenses. The
bank last month posted a 3 percent decline in net income to 10.8
billion rand as revenue slumped and it incurred costs from
firing employees.  Standard Bank’s shares gained 5.4 percent last year, making
it the second-worst performing stock on the six-member FTSE/JSE
Africa Banks Index after  Nedbank Group Ltd. (NED)  The stock closed at
101.76 rand in Johannesburg trading on April 28.  To contact the reporter on this story:
